<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="instruct-vt">instruct <strong><em>vt</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɪn'strʌkt/    美 /ɪn'strʌkt/  </p>
<p>[正式用语]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>教授；指导</strong></h4>
<p>to teach sb sth, or show sb how to do sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We should <strong>instruct</strong> the young not only <strong>in</strong> words, but by deeds. 
我们应该对青年人言传身教。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>指示；命令</strong></h4>
<p>to officially tell sb to do sth (order)：</p>
<ul>
<li>instruct sb to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A computer can only do what you have instructed it to do.
电脑只会做你让它做的事。</p><footer>2009 重庆</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>instruct sb + wh- to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I have been instructed when to start. 
我已得到何时出发的通知。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>[常用于被动语态] 通知</strong></h4>
<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>instructive /ɪn'strʌktɪv/ adj <br />
instructor /ɪn'strʌktə(r)/ n [C]  </p></div>